"""
model.py
========
Deep Neural Network (DNN) encoder — Stage 1 of the hybrid fraud
detection framework.

Paper
-----
"A Hybrid Deep Learning and Explainable AI Framework for Real-Time
Financial Fraud Detection in Dynamic Environments"

Role in the hybrid pipeline
----------------------------
This module implements φ_θ : R^d → R^k, the representation-learning
network whose penultimate layer produces a compact latent embedding

    z = φ_θ(x)  ∈ R^k

that is passed to the gradient-boosted tree ensemble (Stage 2, ensemble.py).

Architecture summary (from paper Section: Proposed Architecture)
-----------------------------------------------------------------
"A tabular encoder, which is a shallow-based multilayer perceptron
trained using dropout and batch normalization, maps the heterogeneous
snapshot to a dense embedding, which encodes cross-feature interactions
not achieved by manual engineering."

"The DNN has three to five fully connected hidden layers that have ReLU
activations and dropout regularizations to deter overfitting.  The
second to last hidden layer produces an embedding of each transaction,
but it is compact, containing high level abstractions of both time and
statistical and engineered features."

Training objective (from paper Section: System Model)
------------------------------------------------------
Parameters θ are trained by minimising a class-weighted cross-entropy
or focal loss:

    L_focal = −Σ [ α·y·(1−p̂)^γ·log(p̂) + (1−α)·(1−y)·p̂^γ·log(1−p̂) ]

with α (class weight) and γ (focusing parameter) tuned to concentrate
gradient mass on minority fraud examples around the decision boundary.

Usage
-----
    # Direct import
    from src.model import FraudDNNEncoder, FocalLoss, train_one_fold

    # Build encoder
    model = FraudDNNEncoder(input_dim=37, embedding_dim=32)

    # Extract embeddings for ensemble (Stage 2)
    z = model.encode(x_batch)            # (B, 32)

    # Full training loop for one fold
    model, history = train_one_fold(
        X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val,
        input_dim=37, embedding_dim=32,
    )

    # Save / load
    model.save("results/models/dnn_fold0.pt")
    model = FraudDNNEncoder.load("results/models/dnn_fold0.pt", input_dim=37)
"""

